  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Integrate SAST with Semgrep in snyk$escape$,
  $escape$To integrate SAST with Semgrep in snyk, navigate to the 'SAST' tab in the snyk UI and click on 'Add SAST provider.' Select 'Semgrep' from the list of available providers. In the 'Semgrep configuration' section, enter your Semgrep API token and specify the repositories to scan. snyk will then use Semgrep to scan your code for security vulnerabilities.$escape$,
